<TITLE> CA sees Bogra breach </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed on Sunday visited the breached stretch of Jamuna flood control embankment at Talukdar Para in Chandanbaisha union under Sariakandi Upazila of Bogra. Fakhruddin toured the area after he had flown to Chandanbaisha by a helicopter around 10:30am. He disbursed relief goods among the affected people and visited the shelter centres. "The affected people have been supplied with relief materials, medicines and places for shelter. Joint forces are cooperating in these activities," the chief adviser later told a press conference. Fakhruddin said authorities had been asked to take permanent measures to fix the breach. "If the work can be started in the winter it is possible to accomplish it in time," he said. "The relevant people have been asked to complete tenders of all development activities by December," he added. Fakhruddin headed for Dhaka around 11am. About 15 metres of the embankment at Talukderpara in Chandanbaisha Union were washed away on Friday night. The breach was only 300 metres away from an earlier damage on Wednesday. bdnews24.
